### 1. Firebase Database Structure
The specific path in your Firebase Realtime Database will look like this:

```json
{
  "iot_system": {
    "control": {
      "reboot": false
    },
    "mq137": 12.5,
    "mq135": 45.2,
    "battery": 85,
    ... other sensor data
  }
}
```

### 2. ESP32 Arduino Code (Copy/Paste this into your `.ino` file)

This code uses the `Firebase ESP32 Client` library. It listens to the database path, checks if `reboot` is `true`, resets the value to `false` (to prevent boot loops), and then executes `ESP.restart()`.

```cpp
#include <WiFi.h>
#include <FirebaseESP32.h>

// 1. CREDENTIALS
#define WIFI_SSID "YOUR_WIFI_SSID"
#define WIFI_PASSWORD "YOUR_WIFI_PASSWORD"
#define FIREBASE_HOST "solanirad-analytics-dashboard-default-rtdb.asia-southeast1.firebasedatabase.app"
#define FIREBASE_AUTH "AIzaSyDrhKHstFwZmBmz4Qd_QZWeCONJjOny9O4" // Your API Key

FirebaseData firebaseData;
FirebaseAuth auth;
FirebaseConfig config;

// Path to listen for reboot command
String rebootPath = "/iot_system/control/reboot";

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);

  // 2. CONNECT TO WIFI
  WiFi.begin(WIFI_SSID, WIFI_PASSWORD);
  Serial.print("Connecting to Wi-Fi");
  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {
    Serial.print(".");
    delay(300);
  }
  Serial.println();
  Serial.println("Connected to Wi-Fi");

  // 3. CONNECT TO FIREBASE
  config.api_key = FIREBASE_AUTH;
  config.database_url = FIREBASE_HOST;

  Firebase.begin(&config, &auth);
  Firebase.reconnectWiFi(true);
}

void loop() {
  // 4. CHECK FOR REBOOT COMMAND
  if (Firebase.ready()) {
    bool shouldReboot = false;

    // Read the boolean value from Firebase
    if (Firebase.getBool(firebaseData, rebootPath)) {
      if (firebaseData.dataType() == "boolean") {
        shouldReboot = firebaseData.boolData();
      }
    } else {
      Serial.println(firebaseData.errorReason());
    }

    // 5. EXECUTE REBOOT LOGIC
    if (shouldReboot) {
      Serial.println("REBOOT COMMAND RECEIVED!");

      // IMPORTANT: Set value back to false BEFORE rebooting 
      // to prevent an infinite reboot loop upon restart.
      if (Firebase.setBool(firebaseData, rebootPath, false)) {
        Serial.println("Reboot flag reset to FALSE.");
      } else {
        Serial.println("Failed to reset flag, but rebooting anyway...");
      }

      delay(1000); // Small delay to ensure DB write completes
      ESP.restart(); // Hard Reset
    }
  }

  // Your sensor reading code goes here...

  delay(1000); // Check every second
}
```

### 3. How the Logic Works
1.  **Dashboard**: When you click the button, React calls `set(ref(..., 'iot_system/control/reboot'), true)`. This turns the switch "ON" in the cloud.
2.  **ESP32**: In its `loop()`, it reads this path. It sees `true`.
3.  **Safety Step**: The ESP32 immediately writes `false` back to that path. If it skipped this step, it would wake up, see `true` again, and reboot forever.
4.  **Restart**: The ESP32 calls `ESP.restart()`, clearing its memory and starting fresh.

